narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Learning in depth about the art surrounding Renaissance warfare. Looked at materials that I would not have considered to be the conventional "art," and I LOVED it.
I learned how to write a historical research paper through the lens of art.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I loved this course. I would have loved a little bit of clearer expectations for the papers and presentations though. I appreciated the freedom, but it was hard to gauge whether our work would miss the mark or not.
I loved that we visited so many different galleries on campus.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: YES take it! Prof Ng is amazing and the course was SO interesting and fun
Yes, because the course not only introduces interesting subject matter, but is a good primer on how to utilize research facilities and resources at Yale.
